that wiped out what they thought would be a financial cushion 
aarp issued a study in conjunction with release of the film that 
showed fewer than half the elderly people eligible for the 
supplemental security income program which is supposed to provide a 
safety net for the poorest of the poor actually get their benefits 
the reasons vary widely from state to state and individual to 
individual but in most cases result from failure of the 
bureaucracy make the program easily available for those too 
unsophisticated or too proud to seek it out 
