closing down failing thrifts and paying off their depositors 
of the 35 percent of respondents who had sampl accounts only 9 
percent said they were withdrawing money because of the industrys 
problems but a fifth said they were considering that step and as 
many said they were holding off on new deposits 
sampls have sustained record withdrawals lately but federal 
analysts have chiefly blamed the higher interest rates that are 
available elsewhere rather than concern about the industrys 
financial problems 
but while the poll found that the sampl crisis had not yet prompted 
many depositors to reduce their accounts others said they were 
