the devastating drought of 1988 is still 
fresh on farmers minds and insurers say theyre getting a bumper 
crop of business this year a lot earlier than usual 
more than 100 million acres of farm land are expected to be 
insured this year compared with about 75 million acres in 1988 
says gene gantz executive director of the american association of 
