<TEXT>
here is a chronology of events 
in el salvadors history over the past 10 years 
oct 15 1979 a group of reformist military officers overthrows 
the rightist government of president gen carlos humberto romero 
cols adolfo arnoldo mejano and jaime abdul gutierrez install a 
junta of themselves and three civilians 
jan 1 1980 civilian junta members resign including social 
democrat guillermo ungo who claims the government is moving too 
slowly to improve social conditions ungo later becomes a political 
leader of the guerrillas 
march 1980 jose napoleon duarte a christian democrat joins 
the junta 
march 24 1980 roman catholic archbishop oscar arnulfo romero 
is assassinated as he celebrates mass linked to the killing is 
roberto daubuisson who the following year founds the rightist 
republican nationalist alliance or arena daubuisson denies the 
charge 
march 30 1980 scores die when gunmen fire on a crowd attending 
romeros funeral 
april 1980 leftist organizations form the democratic 
revolutionary front to become the political wing of the rebel 
movement 
oct 5 1980 five rebel groups form the farabundo marti 
national liberation front 
dec 2 1980 four american women three roman catholic nuns 
and a lay worker are kidnapped their bodies are found in a 
shallow grave dec 4 
dec 5 1980 the united states suspends military and economic 
aid to el salvador pending determination of those responsible for 
the killings four national guardsmen ultimately are sentenced to 30 
years in prison for the murders 
dec 12 1980 duarte is named the first civilian president of 
el salvador in 30 years 
jan 3 1981 the president of the salvadoran institute of 
agrarian reform and two us labor advisers are killed 
march 28 1982 first elections for a national assembly of 60 
seats at stake 24 go to christian democrats 19 to arena and the 
remainder to smaller political groups 
march 25 1984 duarte and daubuisson finish ahead of four 
other candidates in the first round of presidential elections 
guerrillas boycott and threaten violence 
may 6 1984 duarte defeats daubuisson in runoff elections and 
becomes first civilian president chosen by popular vote in 50 years 
march 31 1985 congressional and municipal elections christian 
democrats win 33 of 60 assembly seats 
march 1988 congressional and municipal elections arena takes 
32 of 60 congressional seats 
june 1988 duarte is found to have terminal liver cancer 
jan 24 1989 the guerrillas offer to participate in the 
presidential election and abide by the results if it is postponed 
from march 19 until september and security and antifraud conditions 
are adopted the rebels withdraw the proposal after discussions with 
the political parties fail to achieve progress 
</TEXT>
