<TEXT>
the top judges in connecticuts federal 
district state supreme court and state appellate court are women 
but the members of this unique judicial troika say women still have 
ground to make up 
ellen bree burns is chief judge for the us district court in 
connecticut ellen ash peters is chief justice of the state supreme 
court and antoinette l dupont is chief judge of the appellate court 
the state attorney general also is a woman clarine nardi riddle 
was promoted to acting attorney general when her former boss joseph 
lieberman won a us senate seat in november 
