premier li peng opened the annual session of 
chinas legislature today by calling on chinese to work harder and 
make more financial sacrifices to collectively overcome worsening 
economic woes 
both government and people should be mentally prepared for a 
few years of austerity li told more than 2000 delegates at the 
great hall of the people in central beijing 
he urged officials to give up their vested interests in favor 
of the interests of the whole 
if we set a good example and explain clearly to the people the 
need for tightening our belts they will surely understand and 
support it he said 
