the supreme court today turned away a 
stillpending bigmoney antitrust dispute over the sale of raw milk 
the justices without comment let stand a federal appeals court 
ruling that could cost millions for two cooperative associations of 
dairy farmers and a marketing agent for dairy cooperatives 
the case is nearly 18 years old dating back to a 1971 lawsuit 
filed by one of the dairy cooperatives who ended up an unsuccessful 
defendant in a countersuit 
the 8th us circuit court of appeals in 1982 ruled against 
midamerica dairymen of springfield mo associated milk producers 
inc of san antonio texas and the central milk producers 
cooperative based in chicago 
the appeals court said they had engaged in a broad illegal 
conspiracy to eliminate competitive sellers of grade a raw milk in 
the midwest the appeals court ruled that the conspiracy hurt the 
national farmers organization inc a nationwide farm bargaining 
organization 
the 8th circuit courts 1982 ruling instructed us district 
judge john w oliver in kansas city mo to determine what monetary 
damages nfo should collect 
in ensuing proceedings before judge oliver nfo advanced 
alternative damage measurement theories it claimed tripled damages 
of 554 million under one theory and tripled damages of 222 
million under the other 
the trial judge refused to award any damages 
ruling in the case a second time last july 6 the 8th circuit 
court reaffirmed its holding that nfo incurred substantial 
damages as a result of illegal acts 
the appeals court again sent the case back to oliver with more 
specific directions with respect to the computation of damages 
the appeals court also said the trial judge should determine 
and award appropriate attorneys fees and costs to nfo 
it said oliver was right in rejecting the theory under which nfo 
said it was entitled to 554 million but it said the theory under 
which nfo claimed 222 million in damages is a proper basis for a 
substantial damage award 
the cases are central milk producers cooperative vs national 
farmers organization 881247 and associated milk producers vs 
national farmers organization 881248 
