louis d boccardi president and general 
manager of the associated press has received the paul miller 
journalism award for 1989 
the award was presented march 16 by the oklahoma state university 
school of journalism and broadcasting in honor of miller 82 who 
served as chairman of the associated press and president of gannett 
co inc before his retirement in 1978 
boccardi joined ap in 1967 and was named president and general 
manager in 1985 
boccardi has twice served as a pulitzer prize juror and has been 
elected a distinguished service member of the american society of 
newspaper editors 
he also is a member of advisory boards for the media and society 
seminars gannett center for media studies center for international 
journalism at the university of southern california and the center 
for communications 
miller graduated from oklahoma state in 1931 and joined ap in 
1932 he spent 15 years with the ap before joining gannett in 1947 
as executive assistant to frank e gannett miller was with gannett 
for 31 years the last 16 as president and chief executive officer 
</TEXT>
