<TEXT>
the state department said monday it is prepared 
to support the salvadoran government that emerges from sundays 
national election but only so long as it respects democracy and 
protects human rights 
department spokesman charles redman praised the salvadoran people 
for having braved violence and terror by leftist guerrillas who 
he said tried harder to disrupt sundays balloting than in any 
other election in seven years 
our position is that we support the democratic process that we 
are prepared to support the person who emerges from that democratic 
process redman said 
our relationship with that new government will dependon its 
adherence to democracy and respect for human rights the twin 
pillars of our approach to el salvador 
redman spoke hours before the candidate of the ruling christian 
democratic party fidel chavez mena conceded defeat to alfredo 
cristiani nominee of the rightist arena party 
at the white house presidential spokesman marlin fitzwater said 
judgments about human rights will be a very important factor in 
guiding us policy toward el salvador 
vice president dan quayle also criticized fmln guerrilla attempts 
to disrupt the voting asked by reporters about the deaths of two 
salvadoran and one dutch journalist sunday at the hands of security 
forces quayle said he lacked details 
but what ought to be disturbing to the american people and i 
know its disturbing to the people of el salvador is the fact that 
the fmln threatened the people of el salvador with their lives for 
exercising the democratic right to vote that is a very disturbing 
shocking event and we ouht to be shocked about that quayle said 
after an awards ceremony 
two members of a us delegation sent by president bush to 
observe the election sen mitch mcconnell rky and rep tony 
coelho dcalif said the process appeared to be fair but the 
actions of the new government will decide whether us aid continues 
we concluded that it was a free and fair and honest election 
mcconnell said clearly the activities of the fmln had some impact 
on turnout in some areas of the country 
coelho said the delegation met with cristiani and told him that 
if they return to the death squads return to the killing of the 
early 80s they should not expect support from individuals in our 
legislature as well as our government 
but mcconnell cautioned against applying an unreasonable standard 
we had more murders in this city washington last year than 
they did in the occupied territories of the middle east were not 
in a very good position to be lecturing people about violence he 
said the standard we need to apply here is not to expect that no 
violence will occur in a country in which a war is going on but 
rather how incidents are handled 
meanwhile dozens of demonstrators were removed by police monday 
from a state department entrance as hundreds of others protesting 
us support for the salvadoran government chanted from across the 
street 
the demonstrators did not resist as they were dragged away from 
the diplomatic entrance barricades were then put up and employees 
were diverted to other entrances 
placards and chants accused the united states of supporting 
rightwing death squads 
redman said the government of outgoing president jose napoleon 
duarte was committed to democracy and to improving human rights 
performance 
we will look to the new salvadoran government to uphold the 
same standards and to press for improvement redman said 
the election took place amid growing restiveness in congress 
about american policy in el salvador partly because of the arena 
partys growing strength 
a key figure in the arena hierarchy is maj roberto daubuisson 
who was once described by a former us ambassador to el salvador 
robert white as a pathological killer in 1980 the carter 
administration stripped daubuisson of his us visa 
as administration and congressional sources see it continued 
legislative support for largescale aid for el salvador will depend 
in some measure on cristianis ability to demonstrate that he is 
more than a front man for daubuisson 
although returns are not final cristiani has claimed victory 
over the candidate of the ruling christian democratic party fidel 
chavez mena 
the united states has provided about 35 billion in economic and 
military assistance to el salvador during this decade making it the 
largest recipient of assistance in the hemisphere 
some in congress maintain that the united states has received 
little in return on its investment pointing out that 
politicallymotivated killings average about 20 a month and that 
efforts to negotiate an end to the strife have not succeeded 
the conflict now nearly 10 years old is estimated to have 
claimed about 70000 lives 
