colleges and universities across the country before coming to new 
york for a twoweek run shakespeares shortest play has been made 
even shorter in this production performed at just over two hours 
with no intermission it just seems longer 
director nick ward has a concept but not a play this is bare 
bones shakespeare with no scenery and tattered grimy allpurpose 
costumes eight actors play all the roles when not acting they sit 
trancelike on benches located on three sides of the stage 
that dispassion carries over to their performances ken drury a 
nicol williamson lookalike possesses a resonant voice but it has 
little emotion at least a quivering amelda brown suggests lady 
macbeths obsession with power nothing else in this forlorn revival 
seems alive 
</TEXT>
