<TEXT>
americans made 12 billion person trips in 1987 
according to the us travel data center 
a person trip is travel by one person a distance of 100 miles or 
more from home 
whether they traveled for business or pleasure many depended on 
a travel agent for help 
who are these travel agents 
sharon walker in her 20s works for the ohio motorists 
association travel agency in oberlin ohio its one of 27 
association branches throughout the state 
miss walker headed for the travel business straight out of high 
school lured by her love of travel an interest in geography and 
the prospect of free or cutrate trips a school in florida that 
offered a sixweek crash course plus six months of home study sent 
her on her way 
kaye jones a vice president of barnett travel tours and cruises 
in greensboro nc has been in the business more than 25 years 
she went into the travel field after trying and discarding nursing 
and banking 
jean chipman coowner of the encore preston ii travel agency in 
dallas was divorced and in her 30s when she went to work about 25 
years ago for a friend who owned a travel agency 
it was a traditional business for women without specialized 
training to enter when they wanted something to do after the 
children were grown much like real estate mrs chipman explained 
in a telephone interview 
but computerization has changed all that she said and most 
travel agencies dont have much time for inhouse training these 
days to get a job one needs computer knowhow she also notes that 
more and more men are entering the field especially at management 
level 
both mrs jones and mrs chipman are certified travel counselors 
ctc meaning they have taken courses offered by the institute of 
certified travel agents icta a nonprofit organization 
headquartered in wellesley mass devoted to educating travel 
industry personnel to earn the initials an agent must have 
completed a fivepart travel management program served at least 
five years in the travel industry and signed a code of ethics 
the icta also has started a new program of training in 
geographical areas that will allow agents who complete the course to 
use the desination ds or destination specialist 
a louis harris survey for the american society of travel agents 
asta showed that the gross dollar volume of all bookings handled 
by us travel firms in 1987 was 642 billion 
and yet it seems there is relatively little formal regulation 
in the field 
a spokesman for astas state legislative affairs department says 
only seven states regulate agents and agencies with the regulations 
varying statetostate the seven are california hawaii ohio 
rhode island washington illinois and florida 
various organizations within the industry itself including asta 
have codes of ethics for members astas covers such things as 
accuracy of any information an agent gives out full information to 
travelers about terms and conditions of any sale and prompt 
remittance of any undisputed funds 
the airlines reporting corp is owned by major us airlines and 
serves as a clearing house for receipts that agents get from airline 
tickets they sell it also sets standards for the agents with which 
it has agreements more than 33600 of them if an agency does not 
live up to its agreement arc can pull the plates through which 
it makes out airline tickets 
the icta quotes estimates that there are about 200000 travel 
agents across the country waiting to help travelers usually their 
services are free and they say that especially in this day of 
airline deregulation agents can save the traveler time and money 
with their computers contacts and background 
but how many travelers actually follow the advice to see your 
travel agent 
relatively few according to the travel data center it estimates 
that 13 percent of us travelers consulted an agent in 1987 and of 
those only 10 percent used them to book hotel or airline 
reservations 
asta however estimates that almost 90 percent of cruises are 
booked through travel agencies and 80 percent of airline travel 
but it estimates bookings of hotels through agents only in the 
mid20 percent range with most of that for hotels outside the 
united states 
</TEXT>
