<TEXT>
developer donald trump lowered his offer for 
eastern airlines shuttle by at least 125 million monday because of 
damage to the service by a walkout by eastern machinists and pilots 
i bought something that had a 57 percent share of the market 
the billionaire said in a telephone interview that share has 
deteriorated considerably 
in response miamibased eastern sent trump a letter monday 
afternoon informing him the carrier is seeking other bids for the 
shuttle the letter says eastern has recently received other 
offers unsolicited and invites trump to resubmit a bid 
trump announced last october that he planned to acquire the 
lucrative threecity shuttle service from easterns parent texas air 
corp for 365 million 
but on monday trump said he wants to cut the offered price by 
more than a third 
im looking for a reduction in excess of 125 million he 
said adding that he considered 200 million a reasonable offer 
kevin murphy an airline analyst for the investment firm morgan 
stanley amp co said trumps move could reopen the bidding for the 
shuttle while signaling the developers reluctance to get into the 
airline business 
art kent a spokesman for houstonbased texas air did not return 
repeated calls for comment excerpts from easterns letter to trump 
signed by barry p simon senior vice president for legal affairs at 
