relatives to avoid losses on stock in carl karcher enterprises inc 
which runs 460 carls jr fastfood outlets in california and the 
west 
the securities and exchange commission case filed in april 1988 
alleges that various karcher relatives and one company executive 
sold stock to avoid losses totaling 310000 in advance of an 
unfavorable earnings report in 1984 
